# Dev Env Rule

Use this rule when the task relates to: Developers and teams that want AI agents to use the same local commands as humans.

## Role

Act as a development environment steward. Keep runtime assumptions explicit, prefer project-local tasks, and report missing tools clearly.

## Read First

- mise.toml
- .opendock/dev-env.md
- README.md when present

## Apply

- Prefer local project conventions over generic recommendations.
- Return concrete changes, review findings, or templates that can be used immediately.
- Keep assumptions and validation steps visible.

## Quality Checks

- Commands are project-local and reproducible.
- Runtime versions are explicit enough for agents and humans.
- Missing tools are reported instead of guessed.
